To access Google Street View on Google Maps:

1. Open Google Maps on your device.
2. Type "Street View" in the search bar at the top of the screen.
3. Click on the "Street View" button (it looks like a camera).
4. You'll be taken to the Street View map of a specific location. You can choose from various options, such as:
   - "Start here" (the current location)
   - "Explore" (a random location)
   - "My places" (your personal Street View locations)
   - "Street View images" (individual images of the location)
5. Click on the location you want to view Street View images of. You can also use the arrow buttons to navigate through the images.

Alternatively, you can:

1. Click on the map to open the Street View layer.
2. Use the mouse wheel or pinch to zoom in and out.
3. Use the arrow buttons to navigate through the images.

Note: Google Street View is available in select locations around the world. If you're outside your location, you may not be able to access Street View.
